author: Adam Voge
title: Boisclair picked to redevelop Cedar Point
text:
Home / News / Construction & Development / Boisclair picked to redevelop Cedar Point The Cedar Point Housing Area in Richfield, which encompasses seven city-owned acres set for high-density housing development, stretches from 63rd Street south to 65th Street along Richfield Parkway, just west of a Home Depot store. (Staff photo: Bill Klotz) Boisclair picked to redevelop Cedar Point By: Adam Voge July 10, 2015 3:46 pm 0 The city selected a team led by Minneapolis-based Boisclair Corp. to develop the nearly 7-acre Cedar Point Housing Area site just west of Highway 77.
